step.tex:
\begin{align}

\dfrac{\sin^2 x - \cos^2 x}{\sin^2 x \cos^2 x}
&= \dfrac{\sin^2 x}{\sin^2 x \cos^2 x} - \dfrac{\cos^2 x}{\sin^2 x \cos^2 x}\\
&= \sec^2 x - \mathrm{cosec}^2 x \\
\therefore
\int \dfrac{\sin^2 x - \cos^2 x}{\sin^2 x \cos^2 x}dx 
&= \int ( \sec^2 x - \mathrm{cosec}^2 x ) \, dx \\
&= \tan x + \cot x + C
\end{align}

\begin{align}

\dfrac{\sin^2 x - \cos^2 x}{\sin^2 x \cos^2 x}
&= \dfrac{\sin^2 x}{\sin^2 x \cos^2 x} - \dfrac{\cos^2 x}{\sin^2 x \cos^2 x}\\
&= \sec^2 x - \mathrm{cosec}^2 x \\
\therefore
\int \dfrac{\sin^2 x - \cos^2 x}{\sin^2 x \cos^2 x}dx 
&= \int ( \sec^2 x - \mathrm{cosec}^2 x ) \, dx \\
&= \tan x - \cot x + C
\end{align}

step.reason:
\int \sec^2 x \, dx = \tan x + C_1 \\
\int \mathrm{cosec}^2 x = - \cot x + C_2 \\
\text{where } C_1 \text{ and } C_2 \text{ are constants of integration.}
